- form_for [current_user, @mod] do |f|
  = f.error_messages
  %p= f.label :name
  %p.introduction
    The name of the module.  This should be short, descriptive, and only consist of letters and numbers.
    Once created, the official name for your module will be
    = succeed '.' do
      %b= [current_user.username, '/', '&lt;name&gt;'].join('')
  %p= f.text_field :name
  %p= f.label :source, "Project URL"
  %p.introduction Where can people go to collaborate with you on your module?  If provided, this should be a valid URL.
  %p= f.text_field :source
  %p= f.label :description
  %p.introduction
    Provide some information on your module.
    How do you use it?  Keep it general; you can add notes for specific releases later.
    You can use 
    = link_to "markdown", 'http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/'
    formatting.
  %p= f.text_area :description, :rows => 5
  %p= f.label :tag_list, "Tags"
  %p.introduction A list of comma-separated tags.  This will determine in which categories your module will be listed.
  %p= f.text_field :tag_list
  %p= f.submit(@mod.new_record? ? 'Add module' : 'Update module')